-- Uganda to Get 70% Share of Oil Revenue, Impose Taxes, Daily Monitor Says
-- Fred Ojambo
-- 2010-06-30T05:36:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/uganda-to-get-70-share-of-oil-revenue-impose-taxes-daily-monitor-says.html

          
          
             Uganda ’s government will take an
average of 70 percent of oil revenue, leaving 30 percent for oil
companies, when production starts, the  Daily Monitor  said,
citing Energy Minister  Hillary Onek .  
 Government’s share of the oil revenue will further be
increased with tax levies on the 30 percent share of oil
companies, the Kampala-based newspaper reported.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Fred Ojambo  in Kampala via Johannesburg at
   vwessels@bloomberg.net .  
          
          


  


        